YELLOW FEVER - SOUTH AMERICA (23): ARGENTINA
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sat 12 Apr 2008
Source: JC Online, UOL report [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://jc.uol.com.br/2008/04/12/not_165977.php>


Argentine confirmed a new case of yellow fever [YF] in the region
bordering Brazil, increasing to 6 the number of people affected by
this disease that already killed a person in the country [Argentina,
this year (2008)], said an official on Saturday [12 Apr 2008].

[This case] was a man who lived in the city of Bernardo de Irigoyen,
in Misiones province, on the border with Brazil, indicated a
spokesperson of the provincial Ministry of Health.

This source stated that the state of health of the man was good, and
that he was recovering at home, after having been released by the
Misiones hospital, which is also on the border of Paraguay, where the
disease has killed 8 people this year [2008].

In Brazil, 19 [YF] deaths have been registered between mid-December
[2007] and the end of February [2008] in the center-west region [of
the country].

